assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: COMSYS Holdings Corporation, together with its subsidiaries, engages in telecommunications construction, electrical facilities construction, and information processing-related businesses in Japan. It constructs wired and wireless networks, cable TV and related facilities, access networks, mobile facilities, and electric power facilities; installs, replaces, and removes metal and optic fiber communication cables; installs and replaces utility poles; installs, relocates, and removes communication and information processing equipment in communication stations and data centers; and installs mobile phone base stations and wirings, as well as handles configuration settings and troubleshooting of communication equipment. The company also provides IT solutions and develops software for the private sector and government agencies; equipment wiring, LAN/WAN, network environments, audio systems, and servers/storages; and application development proposals, construction, maintenance, and operations. In addition, it is involved in the water supply and sewerage construction and the design and construction of electrical and telecommunications facilities, as well as the construction of gas-related facilities and solar power/biomass power generation facilities. The company was incorporated in 2003 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
